	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Hunting: Tower of Frozen Shadow</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><br /> Tower of Frozen Shadows<br />
By ellocopato<br />
<br />
The First Floor:<br />
----------------<br />
<br />
Upon entering the tower the first things that you will notice is a huge hole in the floor and many doors. <br />
<br />
Directly infront of you will be a door with two banners hanging from the sides.<br />
Specters called “Lesser Ice Shades” spawn on either side of the door. They have a very slow respawn rate however, remember this door for later reference.<br />
<br />
Traps Warning: <br />
Careful the floor is very slippery and inside the hole are 3 shadowbone skeletons that think you very tasty.<br />
<br />
<br />
Proceed to the second left-hand door, inside this room are many shadowbone skeletons, kill them then camp the hallway of this room. Pull as you like from the other rooms. <br />
<br />
Eventually one of two things will happen: <br />
(1 The Rare will spawn in one of the rooms <br />
(2 The Keyholder will instaspawn once what you’re killing is dead. <br />
<br />
The Keyholder is “A Large Undead Gnoll” and drops the Crystal Key, the key to then next level.<br />
<br />
The Rare is “Xalgoti” a named Shadowbeast, he drops Crystallized Shadow Tunic rarely.<br />
<br />
Grab the key and proceed to the double bannared door previously mentioned. On the left-hand side is a port to the 7th level but needs a key from the boss mob of the tower so skip it for now, and head to the right-hand side. Put the key on your mouse cursor and make sure your entire group is close to you, and hit U (Note for multiple raid groups you’ll need a key for each group it only takes up the groupmembers of the keyholders’ group).<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out:<br />
The mirror out on this floor is right behind of port in.<br />
<br />
The Drops on this level:<br />
Various Gnome Skin Armor (Crappy AC with Poison resist looks like pure black cloth with no designs.)<br />
Various Fading Shadow Weapons<br />
Shadow Bone Earrings (4 Agi 2 Int)<br />
And Various Crystallized Armor (Low ac high stats)<br />
A Crystal Key<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
The Second floor:<br />
-----------------<br />
<br />
Upon port up you will enter an old library filled with Erudite Ghosts. Buff up MR immediately and switch on Resist gear, because nearly everything on this floor casts.<br />
<br />
<br />
Trap Warning:<br />
There is a bookshelf on the right-hand side of the Port Up that screams like a cougar and will claw you. Rogues can disarm this. It will not follow you, so more of a little flavor trap.<br />
<br />
Now you can either sit at port in and pull to there or wander around killing the erudite ghosts. There are way too much spawn on this level to point out but they’re nearly all Necromancers, Magicians, Wizards, or Enchanters. <br />
<br />
There are a few static spawns I should point out, on the booth infront of port in are the Librarian and The Librarian Assistant, these both don’t drop anything special other then crystallized but are named. The second is a hut left of the Port up, inside is a Ghostly Teacher and a Student, both drop nothing.<br />
<br />
Kill the ghosts and eventually one of two things will happen:<br />
(1 the keyholder will instaspawn once your target is dead<br />
(2 The Rare will spawn.<br />
<br />
The Keyholder is “A Angry Librarian” and drops the following<br />
<br />
Angry Librarian:<br />
<br />
The Three Toothed Key (Always)<br />
<br />
Students Homework (Uncommon)<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <br />
+3 INT, +15 MANA, +10 MR<br />
WT: 1.0<br />
Class: NEC, WIZ, MAG, ENC<br />
Race: HUM, ERU, HIE, DEF, HEF, GNM, IKS<br />
<br />
Teacher’s Syllabus (Rare)<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <br />
+3 WIS, +3 INT, +20 MANA, +20 PR<br />
WT: 0.5<br />
Class: CLR, SHM, NEC, WIZ, MAG, ENC<br />
Race: HUM, ERU, HIE, DEF, HEF, DWF, GNM, IKS<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
The rare is “Zorglim the Dead” and drops crystallized pieces uncommonly and sometimes rarely a Crystallized Shadow Tunic.<br />
<br />
<br />
Grab the key and proceed to the next level, to get there head straight out from port in to the door and follow the hallway to the mirror, put the key on your coursor and click U.<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out:<br />
The Mirror Out on this level is on the far left-hand corner, there is a bookshelf, click on it to move it aside but be careful because 2 Students guard behind it. Kill them or run around them and click on the mirror. <br />
<br />
<br />
Drops on this level:<br />
Various Crystallized Armor Pieces<br />
Various Fading and Velium Weapons<br />
Various Gnome Skin Armor.<br />
Teachers Syllabus<br />
Student’s Homework.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
The Third Floor:<br />
----------------<br />
**I need more info on this floor I haven’t been on it very long at all **<br />
<br />
Upon the port up to the Third floor you will find you have entered a creepy manor type décor. <br />
<br />
Trap Warning: No traps on this level that I know of but there are a lot of fake walls.<br />
<br />
Proceed right of the port in area killing anything in the way. Ignore the doors on the sides, sleepers sometimes spawn there but otherwise they are empty. <br />
<br />
Eventually you will come upon a room with Shadowbeast cooks, pull them and kill, turn left and head straight until you come upon a room with a big Table in the middle. Camp here and pull the other rooms to here and eventually one of two things will happen:<br />
<br />
<br />
(1 The Keydropper will instaspawn on what you’re killing.<br />
(2 The Rare will spawn.<br />
<br />
The Keydropper is “An Enraged Shadow Beast” and it drops the following:<br />
<br />
An Enraged Shadow Beast:<br />
<br />
Frosty Key (Always)<br />
<br />
Chilled Scythe (Uncommon)<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <br />
Skill: 2HS Atk Delay: 48<br />
DMG: 23<br />
+4 STR, +4 DEX, +15 HP, 20 MANA, +20 CR<br />
Effect: Shock of Frost<br />
WT: 1.0<br />
Class: WAR, SHD, NEC<br />
Race: ERU, DEF, TRL, OGR, GNM, IKS<br />
<br />
Finely Crafted Velium Ring (Rare)<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <br />
AC: 2<br />
+3 STA, +3 AGI, +15 HP, +8 FR<br />
WT: 0.1<br />
Class: ALL<br />
Race: ALL<br />
<br />
<br />
The Rare is “An Enraged Cook”<br />
<br />
Note: Some people confuse the cook with the enraged beast, I think maybe prepatch they were switched but as it stands now the drop info is correct for the Beast but I’m not sure on the cook. **Need help with Drop info on the Cook**<br />
<br />
Grab the key and proceed to the Mirror to the next floor. Proceed straight up the tunnel that led you to the Dining Room. Ignore any turns and kill anything that jumps you, go straight until you cant anymore then follow the tunnel to the mirror. Put the key on your mouse cursor but make sure your group is good mana and hps cuse the next floor is nasty. Hit U once those conditions have been met.<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out:<br />
Bedroom with zombie maids. Turn right, then left at the shadowbeast room. It's all the way down this hall, last entryway on your right.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Things that drop here:<br />
Various Gnomeskin Armor<br />
Various Crystallized Shadow Armor<br />
Various weapons including crystallized, fading, and velium.<br />
Finely Crafted Velium Ring<br />
Chilled Scythe<br />
Frosty Key <br />
<br />
<br />
The Fourth Floor:<br />
-----------------<br />
<br />
As you port in you will notice you are in a brick maze, it’s mostly like a crypt. Buff your MR and Disease Resistance because The Shadows on this cast nasty spells, and the Ancient Mummies Proc Disease. Make sure to switch on your Resist gear! Be prepared to fight because there are many wanderers<br />
<br />
<br />
Trap Warning: If you go the wrong way there are fake floors that drop you into a room with a few mobs, run into the fire in the center and you will be teleported to the port up area.<br />
<br />
Early Mirror Out:<br />
From the port in on your right is a White door, you can open this with either the key from the previous level or Lockpicks. **not sure skill worked for me at 200 lol** behind it are 3 mobs, kill them or run by them and there is a Mirror at the end of the tunnel, click on it and you will zone out.<br />
<br />
<br />
This maze is tricky, I offer you both a map link and directions<br />
<br />
Link: <a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/mapz/tower_level4.jpg" target="_blank">www.eqmaps.com/mapz/tower_level4.jpg</a><br />
<br />
Directions: <br />
Ignore the white door and take the first right you see, follow this tunnel but ignore the right turn you’ll see, this is a dead end with a mummy. Continue straight and ignore the left turn into a fake wall. Continue straight and you will come upon a single shadow, kill it and make sure you have a lot of mana and health. Next move up or pull the 4 Shadows and fight them. <br />
<br />
When rested head straight through the fake wall where the shadows hung out. There is sometimes a wanderer in this hall, kill it head straight and enter the mummy room. Cara Omica could be spawned in the empty coffin so be prepared. There is also a mummy that spawns in here if I remember correctly. This is your camp area. Sit down and pull the other rooms to you. Infront of you is the mirror to the 5th level, and 4 shadowmen in sets of 2.<br />
<br />
Spawn Order:<br />
Now there are 3 nameds on this level, and this is how I believe you spawn them.<br />
<br />
(1 Pull and kill till Narmak Berreka or his PH spawns. If his PH spawns start over from (1<br />
<br />
(2 When you kill Narmak Amonepheta or his PH will spawn, if his PH spawns kill it and start over from (1<br />
<br />
(3 If you kill Amonpheta, Cara Omica will insta spawn in the coffin. Kill her and she will trigger Narmak Amonpheta or Herself to spawn in a few minutes. <br />
<br />
The Keyholder is “Cara Omica” and she drops the following:<br />
<br />
<br />
Cara Omica:<br />
<br />
A rusty key (Always)<br />
<br />
Embalmers Skinning Knife (Common)<br />
MAGIC ITEM <br />
