<br />
Various weapons including crystallized, fading shadow, and velium.<br />
Various Crystallized Shadow Armor<br />
Various Gnome Skin Armor<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Sixth Level A:<br />
--------------<br />
Upon entering this level you will find many of the same creatures that were on level 1 except a lot harder. Ice shades and Shadow Beasts walk these halls as well as spirits of the undead.<br />
<br />
<br />
Trap Warning: Dragon statue AoE: stay away from the Dragon statue in the room with the ice shades and the mirror out. To know it’s the dangerous one check its hands, if they are flaming and smoking STAY AWAY!!<br />
<br />
Rare Info on this level: <br />
Killing stuff on this level might result in the spawn of<br />
An Incoherent Spirit. Kill him and randomly a Coherent Spirit will spawn. He's for a Kael Drakkal quest, nice reward. He can be found if you go all the way straight from the zonein (to the wall/banner), then turn right and right again.<br />
<br />
A incoherent spirit spawns on level 6 at the aforementioned place, has a rare drop "Abram's Axe of the Stoic", really nice melee weapon. Rare instaspawn off of incoherent's death is an npc quest ghost "lucid spirit of Abram". Part of a long and involved quest from Kael/Wakening. Lucid initially cons indiff to any faction when first spawned but will aggro when attacked and/or if you are fighting a mob near it.<br />
<br />
Proceed to forward killing anything that gets in your way and you come into a hallway with many turns and directions to take. Head right killing anything in your way, or camp here and pull the right till clear. <br />
<br />
Once the beasts are dead proceed up the stairs until you get to a platform above a library. Stay close, don’t fall off or get close to the edge or you will argo the Ice shades below. There are 3 beasts<br />
In the door to the platform, kill them and then rest up. When you are ready have each person on the raid click the mirror (no keys are needed)<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out:<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out on this level is hard to explain, but from port in head straight ignoring the first left, then take a second left. This should hopefully lead you to a room full of ice shades. Invis or pull them and kill. <br />
<br />
Avoid the Dragon Statue AT ALL COSTS stay away from it, it casts a nasty AoE that dropped our fully cleric buffed 53 warrior 2 bubs in seconds. If you are invis, hug the left wall all the way around till you get to the hallway out. Follow the hallway and click on the mirror to be transported out of this hellish room.<br />
<br />
<br />
Drops on this level:<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Sixth Level B:<br />
---------------<br />
<br />
You are transported to a small stone platform with water all around it and a bridge heading upwards.<br />
<br />
Trap Warning: No traps on this level, have fun!<br />
<br />
How To Spawn Vhal Sera <br />
Here is how VhalSera works on the 6B floor. It is a triggered spawn. It does not come from killing bats, which I've done for 6 hours straight thinking that it may spawn.<br />
<br />
When you enter 6A, go straight until you hit the wall. Don't turn at the first intersection. Once you hit the wall, go left to the room with the (8?) ice shades and the Dragon statue AOE trap. Set up camp just before the room so that you don't constantly get hit by the trap, and have a caster pull so no puller gets nailed by the trap either. It will do a large amount of damage and dispell a buff or two.<br />
<br />
The mob that triggers VhalSera to spawn is located in this room (and possibly the other room with ice shades that is located below the mirror to 6B, but I have not confirmed that). I believe the exact name of the ice shades here are "a ice shade". The trigger to make VhalSera to spawn is called "an ice shade" (or if I'm mistaken, it's the other way around). It will look like a Spectre. It won't have a white graphic on its cuffs nor on its hood. It will be straight black, and if you let it stand around for long enough it'll cast a little skeleton pet. It took us a couple spawn rounds to finally get this one to spawn.<br />
<br />
Once killed, VhalSera immediately spawns on 6B. It spawns in the first green floored room, right in the middle (right where the bats like to stand around on top of eachother). Don't forget to make sure that no one is camping 6B or else you're going to spawn the geenie for them and then get fairly pissed off when you go up to find that they profited from your camping. <br />
<br />
One final thing - ID the item(s) on VhalSera. They come out pretty funny.<br />
<br />
If you the shrouded bats that lurk around here, once they are slain killed they spawn Enraged Vampires, which are very mean. <br />
Both mobs process Full Stamina Drain on there target, also the vampires cast many nasty spells including Grav Flux.<br />
<br />
Head up the bridge and proceed through either door, killing all the bats on the way. You will eventually get to a room with a Hand holding a ruby. <br />
<br />
<br />
VhalSera:<br />
Key to the 7th level. (Always)<br />
<br />
Talisman of Vhal Sera (Drop rate unknown)<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <br />
AC: 2<br />
+4 CHA, +3 WIS, +3 INT<br />
WT: 0.0<br />
Class: BRD, SHM, NEC, WIZ, MAG, ENC<br />
Race: HUM, ERU, ELF, HIE, DEF, HEF, GNM, IKS<br />
<br />
<br />
Vhal’Sera Skull Earring (Drop Rate Unknown)<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <br />
AC: 2<br />
+2 STR, +20 HP, +15 MANA<br />
WT: 0.5<br />
Class: ALL<br />
Race: ALL<br />
<br />
Get the key, stand infront of the ruby, and hit U to be transported to the 7th floor.<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out:<br />
The mirror out is below the bridge on the platform next to the water, it transports you back to the port in place of Level 6A.<br />
<br />
Drops on this level<br />
<br />
Vhal’Sera Skull Earring<br />
Talisman of Vhal Sera. <br />
<br />
<br />
The Seventh Floor:<br />
-------------------------<br />
This floor is basically a long black brick corridor. It turns, but there is only one route it can take. <br />
<br />
Traps Warning: <br />
There are some traps near the beginning when you come to a pillar (there is a trap on either side of the pillar). No idea what the trap does as rogue disarmed.<br />
<br />
<br />
Every so often you will come to a drake, these can be pulled solo and were green at 52. <br />
<br />
After about 6 drakes you will come to a doorway on your left that opens to a large(ish) room with a spiral staircase in the middle, and about 6+ spawns around the room. Some of these were blue at 52. If you go up the staircase there are some rooms and a room of mirrors (I believe, warrior scouted). <br />
<br />
However, on the wall opposite where you came into the spiral staircase room is a banner, that is a fake wall. Walk through.<br />
<br />
You will now be in a smallish corridor. It has 4 rooms coming directly off it, one on the left, then one on the right, left then right. At the end is a small circular area where nothing spawns. In each of the 4 rooms a bat spawns, when you kill these there is a chance that the boss of the zone, Tserrina, will spawn.<br />
<br />
Tserrina is level 50, and totally magic resistant. NOTHING would stick to her when we fought her. She blinds, and I heard that she charms sometimes.<br />
<br />
Hint: when we fought her she ran, and because we couldn't get snare to stick she ran back into the spiral staircase room where there was a full spawn =) Managed to kill her tho before we had to evac. I highly suggest you keep that first room clear as you work your way through the 4 bats.<br />
<br />
The Mirror Out<br />
<br />
There are serveral mirrors out in the room with many mirrors.<br />
<br />
Drops on this floor:<br />
<br />
Harnessed Soul Gem<br />
